Subject: Preserve an existing generated libc++ header directory

LLVM's build product prepares a system C++ header symlink before CMake runs.
Nucleus builds libc++ through LLVM_ENABLE_RUNTIMES, and that configure replaces
the symlink with a real generated include/c++ tree. A later incremental
invocation must retain that tree: `ln -s -f` cannot replace a directory and,
if the caller deletes it first, an invocation without --reconfigure leaves the
new symlink pointing at the system libstdc++ headers. Skip the bootstrap
symlink when the destination already exists as a directory.

Sentinel: NUCLEUS_SWIFT_SOURCE_PRESERVE_GENERATED_LIBCXX_HEADERS

diff --git a/utils/swift_build_support/swift_build_support/products/llvm.py b/utils/swift_build_support/swift_build_support/products/llvm.py
index 896af262c..0816d07bf 100644
--- a/utils/swift_build_support/swift_build_support/products/llvm.py
+++ b/utils/swift_build_support/swift_build_support/products/llvm.py
@@ -510,6 +510,12 @@ class LLVM(cmake_product.CMakeProduct):
         built_cxx_include_dir = os.path.join(self.build_dir, 'include')
         if not os.path.exists(built_cxx_include_dir):
             os.makedirs(built_cxx_include_dir)
+        cxx_include_path = os.path.join(built_cxx_include_dir, 'c++')
+        # NUCLEUS_SWIFT_SOURCE_PRESERVE_GENERATED_LIBCXX_HEADERS
+        # LLVM_ENABLE_RUNTIMES populates this as a real directory after the
+        # initial configure. Preserve it on incremental invocations.
+        if os.path.isdir(cxx_include_path) and not os.path.islink(cxx_include_path):
+            return
         print('symlinking the system headers ({}) into the local '
               'clang build directory ({}).'.format(
                   host_cxx_headers_dir, built_cxx_include_dir), flush=True)
